METHODS:

There will be times when you will want to prevent a methods to be overridden.
To disallow a method being overridden, specify the FINAL as a modifier at the start
of its declaration.
METHOD DECLARED AS FINAL CANNOT BE OVERRIDDEN
* Sometimes provide a performance enhancement

CLASSES:
Use final to prevent Inheritance
You can declare a CLASS FINAL, preventing it from being inherited.
Declaring a class as FINAL implicitly declares all of its methods as FINAL too
IT IS ILLEGAL TO DECLARES A CLASS AS BOTH ABSTRACT AND FINAL SINCE AN ABSTRACT
CLASS IS INCOMPLETE BY ITSELF AND RELIES UPON ITS SUBCLASSES TO PROVIDE COMPLETE
IMPLEMENTATIONS